  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Zest the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Roughly break up the <strong>walnuts</strong>&nbsp;in a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong> or chop them roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter&nbsp;</strong>over a high&nbsp;heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>spring onion</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and&nbsp;the <strong>walnuts</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 2-3 min or until brown and crispy&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, stir in the <strong>lemon zest</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt </strong>- this is your <strong>walnut crumble&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Transfer it to a plate and keep the pan for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>mushrooms</strong> into thick slices</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong>&nbsp;to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;with a large pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the linguine,&nbsp;<strong>reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the&nbsp;pan to a medium heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>mushrooms&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 2-3 min or until they've browned</p>\r\n<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>shaoxing</strong>&nbsp;<strong>wine</strong> and cook 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the&nbsp;reserved&nbsp;<strong>pasta water</strong> to the mushrooms</p>\r\n<p>Crumble the <strong>blue cheese</strong> into the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has a creamy consistency, then set aside</p>\r\n<p>Cut and juice half of the <strong>lemon</strong> straight into the pan&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/802.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
